stack: TypeScript, Node.js, Bash

@EXPORTS
make-admin.ts: makeAdmin — promote user to admin by email
sync-lesson-titles.ts: syncTitles — sync chapter titles from static data to DB
update-avatar-paths.mjs: updateAvatarPaths — fix avatar image paths in DB
generate-grain-svg.js: generateGrainSVG — generate grain texture SVG for UI
generate-grain-texture.js: generateGrainTexture — generate grain texture as image
kubernetes/deploy.sh: deploy — K8s deployment script
kubernetes/create-secrets.sh: createSecrets — create K8s secrets from env vars
kubernetes/create-sealed-secrets.sh: createSealedSecrets — create sealed secrets for GitOps
kubernetes/create-postgres-sealed-secret.sh: createPostgresSecret — create DB connection sealed secret
migration/import-postgres-data.ts: importData — import data from SQLite to PostgreSQL
migration/archive/export-sqlite-data.ts: exportData — export data from old SQLite DB
migration/verify-migration.ts: verifyMigration — verify data migration integrity

@PROCESSES
MakeAdmin: `tsx scripts/make-admin.ts <email>` → set isAdmin=true on user
Migration: export-sqlite-data → import-postgres-data → verify-migration
K8sDeploy: create-secrets → deploy.sh → apply K8s manifests

@DEPENDENCIES
internal: @/lib/prisma (make-admin, sync-lesson-titles)
external: tsx, pg

@WARNINGS
- migration/archive/export-sqlite-data.ts is for one-time migration — do not reuse
- K8s scripts reference specific Harbor registry & namespace
